description:
This is a collection of releases of the most talented Russian indie bands. All of them sing on English and they really deserve to be checked out.


\&quot;My rockets up\&quot; - \&quot;Humanaut\&quot; [2007] &lt;a href=&quot;
http://www.myspace.com/mojrakety&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://www.myspace.com/mojrakety&lt;/a&gt;
It\&amp;#039;s an experienced post-rock band, whose members collaborate since late 90s. In Netherlands and Australia the band is also known as \&quot;Moj Rakety\&quot;. \&quot;Humanaut\&quot; is their third studio album.

\&quot;Dustveil\&quot; - \&quot;Sentimental Lies\&quot; EP [2007] &lt;a href=&quot;
http://www.myspace.com/dustveil&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://www.myspace.com/dustveil&lt;/a&gt;
FOUNDED IN: 2001, the band split in 2004 and re-gathered in 2005
STYLE: Indie-rock / art-rock / post-rock with occasional elements of jazz, an electronic drum section and effects.
IDEA: To sweep the dustveil off certain values

\&quot;Everything Is Made In China\&quot; - [self-titled EP] [2006]
\&quot;Everything Is Made In China\&quot; - \&quot;4\&quot; [2007] &lt;a href=&quot;
http://www.myspace.com/playreunion&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://www.myspace.com/playreunion&lt;/a&gt;
\&quot;Everything is made in China\&quot; is one of the most talented Russian indie-bands. They\&amp;#039;re infuenced by Smashing Pumpkins, Radiohead, etc. and perform very melodic post-rock. \&quot;4\&quot; is their debute album, and it\&amp;#039;s definitely worth listening.

\&quot;Where Are You, Liam?\&quot; - \&quot;61\&quot; EP [2006] &lt;a href=&quot;
http://www.myspace.com/whereareyouliam&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://www.myspace.com/whereareyouliam&lt;/a&gt;
The name of this band from Nighni Novgorod was found during Oasis\&amp;#039;s gig, when Noel Gallagher had to sing all the songs alone. \&quot;Where are you, Liam?\&quot; performs psychedelic indie-rock.

\&quot;Silence Kit\&quot; - \&quot;The Great Red Spot\&quot; [2007] &lt;a href=&quot;
http://www.myspace.com/silencekitmoscow&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://www.myspace.com/silencekitmoscow&lt;/a&gt;
Instrumental music, performed by \&quot;Silence Kit\&quot;, indie-rock band from Moscow, sounds very special, due to the band\&amp;#039;s experiments with the sound.

\&quot;Klever\&quot; - \&quot;In The Name Of Peace And Progress\&quot; [2005] &lt;a href=&quot;
http://www.myspace.com/kleverrr&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://www.myspace.com/kleverrr&lt;/a&gt; 
\&quot;KLEVER\&quot; - is a group from St. Petersburg, playing instrumental music, which can be characterised (if it is so necessary to do) as psychedelic-independent-music. They do not copy or styling up different folk traditions - they see their task in something else. Every of the group members bring something of their own, a particle of their unic view of the world and music. And it happens spontaneously, without mutual agreement about a certain style or the manner of playing.
